India Equity Movers: Bharat Heavy, Motilal Oswal, Nova Iron

-- B y   A m e y a   K a r v e
-- 
2011-06-09T11:28:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/india-equity-movers-bharat-heavy-motilal-new-delhi-television.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  India  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of the 3:30 p.m. close in Mumbai.  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or Sensex, was
little changed at 18,384.9. The BSE 200 Index was also little
changed at 2,286.42.  Bharat Heavy Electricals Ltd. (BHEL)   increased 1.1
percent to 1,933.2 rupees, the steepest gain almost a month.
India’s biggest power equipment maker is bidding for contracts
in Iraq, Iran and  Africa  seeking to double the value of overseas
orders by 2016. “In five years, we want to reach 76 billion
rupees ($1.7 billion)” in orders from overseas, Chairman B. Prasada Rao said yesterday in an interview at his New Delhi
office.  Infrastructure Development Finance Co. (IDFC IN) fell 1.5
percent to 134.25 rupees, its lowest in two weeks. The lender to
power and road projects fell as 11.5 million shares changed
hands in two separate block deals on the Bombay Stock Exchange
and the National Stock Exchange, according to the data compiled
by Bloomberg. Buyers and sellers weren’t immediately known.  Motilal Oswal Financial Services Ltd. (MOFS)   added 1.6
percent to 103.55 rupees, the steepest climb in almost two
weeks. The stock brokerage has cut 100 jobs and may pare more as
trading volumes dwindle, the Economic Times reported, citing
officials it did not identify.  Nova Iron & Steel Ltd. (NIS)   jumped by its daily limit
of 4.9 percent to 12.79 rupees. Bhushan Power & Steel Ltd.
bought 22.25 million shares of the company, Bombay Stock
Exchange data showed. Nova Corp., Veena Gambhir and Sunita
Gambhir sold stakes in Nova Steel, according to the exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ameya Karve in Mumbai at 
 akarve@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net . 